Contrast lookup.ts:7 `fetch(url, { signal: AbortSignal.timeout(TIMEOUT) })` and weather.ts:26 `fetch(url, { signal: AbortSignal.timeout(5000) })`. If Telegram's API stalls the connection after handshake (e.g. firewall drops packets), the awaited promise never settles; the catch on line 21 never fires, and callers such as meeting_reminder/index.ts:192 `await sendTelegram(...)` hang. Fix: add `signal: AbortSignal.timeout(5000)` to the options and return `{ ok:false, channel:"telegram" }` on the resulting AbortError.

